  "prompt": "What universities does Lakeland Financial recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Lakeland Financial, which is the parent company of Lake City Bank, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, particularly those that are located in Indiana and the surrounding Midwest region. They tend to focus on schools that have strong finance, business, and economics programs.\n\nIn terms of majors, Lakeland Financial often looks for candidates with degrees in:\n\n- Finance\n- Accounting\n- Business Administration\n- Economics\n- Marketing\n- Management\n- Information Systems\n\nThey may also consider graduates from related disciplines, depending on the specific roles available. To get the most accurate and updated information regarding their recruitment practices and preferred universities, checking their official website or career fairs and job postings is advisable.",
